description:
Hello , I am an interior designer. I hope you will enjoy staying in my happy place :) Located on 15th Street at Park Ave. 

My 1 bedroom apartment is on the top floor of an old townhouse located right in Union Square. Close to every train line, Whole Foods, and the Union Square Farmers Market. 

Fun Fact: I am currently building a steam room in the unit that will be completed by March 2017.

Located in a charming historic townhouse I have turned the top floor into my version of a jewelry box. There are two sky lights in the apartment. One of which is located above the shower- giving you a outdoor shower experience. 

The bedroom is decorated in a peaceful white and beige palate. Paired with a comfortable queen sized Casper mattress.  

The Kitchenette is equipped with a Nespresso machine, electric tea kettle, and a hot plate- pots and pans. No sink in the kitchenette.

Located on 15th Street at Park Ave. 

Please note: No shoes inside the apartment. :)

I am always a call or text away. My goal is to make your stay perfection.

review.comments: Julie's Union Square apartment is steps away from the subway, linking you to routes all across NYC. It's a great jumping off point for exploring. She has a creative and clever sense of style giving the apartment lots of charm. She was also very easy to reach via text messaging. We loved our stay!
